<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>But you overdramatize, and missed my point.</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Min">Min</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 5:11 p.m. 10/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> But you overdramatize, and missed my point.<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=640" TARGET=_self>Again, you miss the point.</A> (The RealmWeaver)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>> You are overlooking the entire point. The goal is to AVOID

<BR>&gt; having to split the game into two seperate, opposed communities.
<BR>&gt; This is the last post I will make on the subject to you as you
<BR>&gt; are apparently blind to what I am trying to say, or accomplish.
<P>Yes it is partially split, but it's not as bad as you think, right now even if there is a split there are few animosity between -PvP and +PvP groups because -PvP feels safe, they feel that they can play the game without having to deal with the childish part of the society. If you try to infringe on their environment you will _really_ see a split between the 2 communities(things like you see in UO) which will destroy the fragile truce between -PvP and +PvP right now. It depend on whether you want to satisfy a small group and piss off a bigger group.
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
